<body>
  
  
  <bookmark branch="hid/.uno:AddField" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3149182"/><paragraph id="hd_id3144436" role="heading" level="1" oldref="1" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US"><link href="text/shared/02/01170400.xhp" name="Add Field:">Add Field:</link></paragraph>
  <paragraph l10n="U" role="paragraph" id="par_id3166460" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="2"><variable id="text"><ahelp hid=".uno:AddField" visibility="visible">Opens a window where you can select a database field to add to the form.</ahelp></variable></paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3147242" l10n="E" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="" localize="false"><link href="text/shared/00/00040501.xhp#feldhinzu" name=""><embedvar href="text/shared/00/00000004.xhp#wie"/></link></paragraph>
  <bookmark branch="hid/HID_FIELD_SEL" xml-lang="en-US" id="bm_id3155503"/><paragraph l10n="U" role="paragraph" id="par_id3156114" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="3"><ahelp visibility="visible" hid="HID_FIELD_SEL">The field selection window lists all database fields of the table or query that was specified as the data source in the <link href="text/shared/02/01170201.xhp" name="Form Properties">Form Properties</link>.</ahelp></paragraph>
  <paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3147620" l10n="U" xml-lang="en-US" oldref="4">You can incorporate a field into the current document by dragging and dropping it into the document while holding down the mouse button. A corresponding field is then set up in the document with a link to the database.</paragraph>
  <paragraph xml-lang="en-US" role="paragraph" id="par_id3153541" l10n="U" oldref="5">If you switch off the <link href="text/shared/02/01170500.xhp" name="Design Mode">Design Mode</link>, you can see that $[officename] sets up a labeled input field for every inserted database field where the user can enter the data.</paragraph>
 </body>
